race.comment: PAW VADA (4) was below best at her last couple, the latest finishing fourth at Geelong, but was among the placings at Horsham three back. Can make amends this time. ASTON SURPRISE (1) finds it hard to break through. Hit the board with a minor placing last time when third (25.70) at this track. Solid record here winning two races. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Can measure up. CRACKERJACK HOPS (6) has a strong winning strike-rate here having won two of three starts. Placed last time (26.12) at Geelong in a Grade 5, finishing third and beaten one length. With even luck and a clean start should be thereabouts. MR. FRANKIE LEE (2) won by a wide margin last start. That form reads well. Something for the Multiples: RUCKMAN (3)
